@NODE "mail_137" " AmySequencer: how to use "
From: Stefano Maria Regattin <esseerre@...>
Date: 02-07-02 00:33:00
Subject: @{b}AmySequencer: how to use@{ub}

Date: Thursday, 7th February 2002

Hi Blitz users!
Here are the instruction for use AmySequencer:
1) select the voice "sound editor" from the "windows" menu.
2) load a 8svx mono sample using the menu of the sounds editor window.
3) click on the name of the sample in the sounds editor window to assing to
it a channel.
4) close the sounds editor window.
5) now select the voice "notes editor" from the "windows" menu.
6) click on the channel number assigned to the sound; they must have the
same colour.
7) draw a note; if you have do all right, you should hear the sound.
8) try add more notes; use the zoom button (it is placed where the two
sliders meet, Zn, where n is the zoomout factor)
9) select one or more note; a selected note is like "X", a not selected note
is "[]"
10) now experiment change the properties of the selected notes, using the
cursor keys and the shift keys.
11) if you are satisfied you can hear all the note toghether selecting
"play" from the notes editor menu.
Have fun!

