@NODE "mail_145" " Re: BeginRefresh...EndRefresh "
From: Demon Hell <demonhell_@...>
Date: 02-16-02 19:13:20
Subject: @{b}Re: BeginRefresh...EndRefresh@{ub}


>I want to use simplerefresh windows with some
>self drawen gfx on it. The gfx is very complex
>and I don't want to redraw all of it. So I use
>BeginRefresh/EndRefresh pair. It sets up a layer
>so that only the damaged part of window is redrawn.
>But I also want to know which area of the window is really
>affected to optimize the redrawing more.
>OK, I receive the #IDCMP_REFRESHWINDOW message
>and now I want to know the Coordinates where to
>redraw the window exactly. Any ideas ?

AFAIK the IDCMP_REFRESH message is simply that..a message to say your window 
display needs redrawing. Any prog can trash the rastport/bitmap for any 
window so there`s no way to tell what area needs redrawing without having a 
duplicate bitmap and comparing the 2.

A simpler way might be just to double buffer the window.
Ie do all the drawing to a bitmap, when it`s done copy that to the windows 
bitmap..then when you get a refresh message, simply copy the original bitmap 
to the window again.

