Hello amorel

Come on!
I can give you an include file (like the image.include)
were you can do camd stuff like this:

-------------------------------- BEGIN PROGRAM
If camd_add_sender {camdport.w,"mycamdcluster.0"}
  ...
  camd_send {camdport.w, data_ptr.l, bytelength.l}  ; send mididata
  camd_send {camdport.w, data_ptr.l, bytelength.l}  ; send some more
  ...
  camd_free {}
End If
-------------------------------- END PROGRAM

Easy, isn't it ? You need 3(!) statements to init, use and free the
camd.library.
It checks everything for you, e.g. if camd.library is installed.
You can open as many camd connections as you like (max=256), no
problems with incompatible serial.devices.

Receiving is done like that:

-------------------------------- BEGIN PROGRAM
If camd_add_receiver {camdport.w,"mycamdcluser.0"}
  camd_sigflag.l = camd_sigflag {}

  While  quitme.w = false
     singals.l = wait_ (whateversignalsyouwanttowaitfor | camd_sigflag)
     If camd_receive {}
       statusbyte.b = camd_received_status {}
       databyte1.b = camd_received_dat1 {}
       databyte2.b = camd_received_dat2 {}
       camdport.w = camd_received_port {}
       timestamp.l = camd_received_time {}
       ...
     End if
  Wend

  camd_free {}
End If
-------------------------------- END PROGRAM

Big advantage is that you don't have to get the received bytes in
realtime, you can set a pointer to your timestamp variable
and every received data will have a timestamp. The timestamp
will be drawn from YOUR counter, so you can use any format
for timestamp you want. Plus you only have to check once
if you have several connections open.

Think twice about it, using devices is like writing only Paula audio output,
using camd is like using AHI, you can be sure that new camd drivers
will appear for camd and not for devices (e.g. Soundblaster MIDI/Gameport).
Plus there will be a camd driver that is configurable to wrap output to
devices,
so every serial port that has a serial.devices will be supported by camd
as well.
You can also benefit from other camd software like softynths or traffic
monitors.

Interessted ?

