@NODE "mail_215" " GTLists and memory loss - SUMMARY "
From: Thilo Köhler <koehlerthilo@...>
Date: 02-26-02 13:45:48
Subject: @{b}GTLists and memory loss - SUMMARY@{ub}

All you guys have to read a bit more carefully.
So I do a summary:

Memory Loss 1:  Old BBGTLib
In the older version of BBGTLib was a memory loss
if you use GTCycle gadgets in a GTList. Strangely it was
not everytime you free a GTList, it was about every second time.
This is definetly a bug in the BBGTLib.

Memory Loss 2:   New BBGTLib
In the newest version of BBGTLib is a memoryloss every time
when you use a GTList, no matter what kind of buttons.
A simple GTList with one button looses 112bytes(depending on the
text length in the button), a complex one
can loose about 3kb each time.
This is definetly a bug in the BBGTLib.

Memory Loss 3:  MCP
If you use MCP and have the Cycle2Menu option turned on,
you loose everytime you select a new option in the Cyclegadget
via pull down menu exactly 64bytes.
This is definetly a bug in MCP.


I hope you got it now.
As I regard the BBGTLib as one of the most important ones
I would be happy to see this bug fixed. Using OS functions
is no solution because this is not the idea of BlitzBasic, and
you miss features like Debugger and auto freeing on exit.

Ciao,

Thilo

