Well if your case realy is the add one to allready sorted list then 
best way is to find the two items, which are going to be before and 
after the item you are adding. this will give you linear worst case 
(the place to add is the first place in the array, so you need to move 
all the rest one place up).

If you know that you need constant adding of items, then you might 
collect a bunch of elements and add them with one sweep through the 
array.

PS. Finding a place where to add is always faster than using add 
tail/head & sort type of thing when you only need to add one item.


